<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Route should allow for all types of URI characters (as per RFC 3986).
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URL_encoding">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/URL_encoding</a></p>

<p>Reported by Michael Sheakoski and Kirill Balyasnikov.</p>

<p>Here is the regex for full RFC 3986 support:</p>

<pre class="literal">
const DEFAULT_REGEX = '[a-z0-9\-\_\.\~\!\*\'\(\)\;\:\@\&amp;\=\+\$\,\?\%\#\[\]]+';
</pre>

<p>All characters are accounted for except {{/}} for obvious reasons :)
-Michael Sheakoski</p>

    </div>
